      <description>&lt;DIV&gt;[Tue Sep 26 23:43:20 2006] You say, 'nymphs'&lt;BR&gt;[Tue Sep 26 23:43:20 2006] Hanook says 'The story is not too complex, and I can give it to you simply.&amp;nbsp; Tunare loved her children, the Takish-Hiz.&amp;nbsp; Solusek Ro was jealous of her children, so he raised the Serpent Spine to deny the Elddar Forest the water it would need to survive.&amp;nbsp; When Tunare saw what became of her children she wept.&amp;nbsp; Where her tears fell, soon after a Nymph rose from the element where they fell.&amp;nbsp; They Dryads rose from the trees that the tears fell on, the Oread from the stones of the ground, the Potameid from the rivers and ponds, and the Napaea from the grasses they so love.&amp;nbsp; We have each become attuned to the element from which we sprang.'&lt;BR&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;</description>
