      <title>On Mayong and Immortality</title>
      <link>http://eqforums.station.sony.com/eq/board/message?board.id=Lore&amp;message.id=12059#M12059</link>
      <description>Mayong is probably SoE's most interesting character, vampires are usually interesting in fiction anyway when they are done right. (DESTROY ANN RICE) Ancient vampires such as Mayong are probably the most interesting because they see their fictional world and they know the past and you have to ask just what is Mayong's goal.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;His character is the embodiment of corruption if their ever was one. Vampires are undead and a corruption of the living, but even more so Vampires are probably what most people think of, when they think of immortal undead. Now a skeletal guardian or somesuch that guards a tomb is immortal but he does not experience life in a way that the word mortal signifies. A lich? Possibly, but then again he cannot have relationships and they seem to almost always be preoccupied with the higher studies into magic rather than playing events to their whim. Liches in most fiction want to be left alone in some swamp or four hundred feet below the ground and if you disturb them, they will mess you up. But these types of immortals do no seek the living actively and definately do not seek to control political/historical happenings.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;So whatever race Mayong was, is uncertain. What is certain is that if he was around during the first days of veeshan's dragons, he is not any of the current gods' creation. What's uncertain is how he attained his vampiric state. Most magical research leads to liches so either some sort of artifact turned him into a vampire or another vampire turned him into a vampire. For me, I'm going to have to lean on the artifact idea. I'm not sure what artifact, I'm not even saying Shadowspine because even the last guy that got it (the guy defending the city or whatever) got lich'd.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;His rise to demi-godhood was probably the best display of corruption there is what with taking over somebody elses plane and enslaving its inhabitants. Also, I think the only reason he likes dark elves is because they are a corruption of the Elddar. Maybe he sees potential in them since he, as a corrupted being has gained so much power and he could possibly use Tier'dal more than any other race to control? Kinda like since they are born of corruption alot of the dirty work is done for him already? Not sure though.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;He was necessary for entombing Kerafyrm as I think I recall from game lore. The dragons basically employed him to do it as he had no love for them, curious as to what they traded him for this serious procedure. (i'm sure SoE will have to think something up for this, but that's ok)&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Kerafyrm didn't wrong him, if anything Kerafyrm doesnt even realize mayong's involvement in his entombing (you don't blame the guy for building the coffin that someone else put you in.)&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;So..speculations as to what artifact empowered him/what person turned him into a vampire and who wrong him?&lt;br&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</description>
