      <title>City corruption: Qeynos and Freeport</title>
      <link>http://eqforums.station.sony.com/eq/board/message?board.id=Lore&amp;message.id=12050#M12050</link>
      <description>&lt;DIV&gt;Which city is more corrupt?&amp;nbsp; My vote goes to Qeynos.&amp;nbsp; While Freeport is more open with their problems, Qeynos is prone to hiding them.&amp;nbsp; &lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;Qeynos:&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;The poor peole have been forced into the sewers in order to improve city life for the richer folk&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;Citizens talk abot dead bodies washing up on the shore&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;Guards threaten players, and ask for bribe money&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;Home of the largest rogue guild on Norrath, with connections to Carson in Highpass&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;City on the edge of a revolt lead by Commander Kane.&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;Tax way too high for citizens, as they so claim.&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;Freeport:&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;Knights of truth casuing dissent within the city&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;Tax collecters skimming off the top in taxes&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;Corrupt guards known to turn a blind eye to crime&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;Although Freeport has poor beggers running amok, Qenos seems to be the "evil" city, despite the fact that it's the supposed jewel of humanity.&amp;nbsp; &lt;/DIV&gt;</description>
